        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 11:37PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1137 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Buffalo, or near Lafayette, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke, Lafayette, Stroud, La Fayette, Lakeview, Five Points, Post
Oak Forks, Denson, Amity Park, Abanda, Welch, Trammel Crossroads,
Buffalo, Chambers County Lake, Fredonia, Veasey Creek Park, Crystal
Lake, Penton, Huguley, and Dickert.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
